  "text": "Calculating entity similarity lies at the heart of knowledge-rich approaches to computing semantic similarity, a fundamental task in Natural Language Processing and Information Retrieval [CITATION_1] . As previously mentioned, in the feature embedding space semantically similar entities appear close to each other in the feature space. Therefore, the problem of calculating the similarity between two instances is a matter of calculating the distance between two instances in the given feature space. To do so, we use the standard cosine similarity measure, which is applied on the vectors of the entities.",
